<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-31T10:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-31T10:29:00-05:00" n="453" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d453">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/8732</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-31T18:00:00+02:31">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 31, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received February 3, 4.11
                                a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2309. Your 2014. French Ambassador informs us that he received no
                            instructions from his Government to protest against retaliatory measures
                            against Rumanian subjects in Russia. As he of course participated in
                            joint protest of Diplomatic Corps against arrest of Rumanian Minister
                            and as the latter has now been expelled from Russia<note n="1" xml:id="d453fn1">For the further developments in relations between
                                Russia and Rumania, see <ref target="frus1918Russiav02">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi></ref>, chap. v.</note> further
                            action or protest appears to be useless.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>